## Live read-only assessment

```bash
ansible-playbook playbooks/run.yml -i playbooks/inventory \
  -e zos_live_assessment=true -e zos_target=<zos-lpar-host>
```

Live mode runs the verify commands via `ibm.ibm_zos_core` (`zos_operator` for
`D ...` displays, `zos_tso_command` for TSO/RACF commands) and writes the raw
output to `{{ zos_slug | default('zos') }}_live_evidence.json` for the ATO package.
It requires z/OS Python + ZOAU + SSH on the target LPAR and an automation user
with the authority to issue the (read-only) commands.
